===Phonosemantic interpretation===

[[w:Old_Chinese|Old Chinese]] [[w:Old_Chinese_phonology#Initials|Initial]] {{IPAchar|/*k-/}} lends semantic value '''Frame'''. [[w:Old_Chinese_phonology#Vowels|Vowel]] {{IPAchar|/*-ua-/}} lends semantic value '''Curving/Round'''.
[[w:Chinese_character_classification#Phono-semantic_compound_characters|Phono-semantic indicator]] [[囗]] circular enclosure (here suggesting an enclosed parcel of land) + [[w:Radical_(Chinese_character)#Semantic_elements|semantic indicator]] [[戈]] spear/halberd → defend enclosed land/an enclosure. Present-day meanings are [[w:Chinese_characters#Transformed_cognates|borrowings]].
Source: [http://www.kanjinetworks.com/eng/kanji-dictionary/online-kanji-etymology-dictionary.cfm?kanji_id=KUAKx04 Howell & Morimoto]

===Etymology===
{{Han compound|戈|口|一|ls=ic}}.

Note that [[咸]] is not derived from 或, and that the characters 口一 are stacked in the opposite order in these characters. Both are ultimately from {{term|戈||halberd, spear|sc=Hani}}.

